Subject: [PATCH 362/587] usbhid: call usb_fixup_endpoint after mangling
 intervals

Lets the mousepoll override mechanism work with xhci.

Signed-off-by: Jonathan Bell <jonathan@raspberrypi.org>
---
 drivers/hid/usbhid/hid-core.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/hid/usbhid/hid-core.c b/drivers/hid/usbhid/hid-core.c
index bca16660ef9d..562795a1bd48 100644
--- a/drivers/hid/usbhid/hid-core.c
+++ b/drivers/hid/usbhid/hid-core.c
@@ -1115,6 +1115,7 @@ static int usbhid_start(struct hid_device *hid)
 				interval = hid_kbpoll_interval;
 			break;
 		}
+		usb_fixup_endpoint(dev, endpoint->bEndpointAddress, interval);
 
 		ret = -ENOMEM;
 		if (usb_endpoint_dir_in(endpoint)) {
